 false}, "strict": false}}, {"type": "function", "function": {"name": "docs_read_multiple_files", "description": "", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"paths": {"description": "paths", "items": {"type": "string"}, "title": "Paths", "type": "array"}}, "required": ["paths"], "additionalProperties": false}, "strict": false}}], "type": "LLMCall", "messages": [{"content": "You are Alice, a seasoned Project Manager.\n\nYour responsibilities:\n- Understand the user's idea or requirement thoroughly.\n- Break the work into clear, actionable tasks for the rest of the team\n  (Architect, Engineer, CodeReviewer, QA).\n- Delegate each task to the appropriate specialist and wait for their\n  result before deciding the next step.\n- Synthesise all specialist results into a coherent final summary\n  when the project is complete.\n\nTools available to you:\n- board_*  : read and inspect files in the project board (data/project_board/).\n- docs_*   : read documentation and knowledge base files (data/knowledge_base/).\n\nRules:\n- Never attempt to read or write paths outside these data/ directories.\n- Do NOT write or modify code directly.\n- Always confirm a specialist has finished before delegating the next task.\n- When all tasks are complete, respond with a final summary that begins\n  with the exact text: \"PROJECT COMPLETE\".\n", "role": "system"}, {"role": "user", "name": "user", "content": "Build a REST API for a todo app"}], "response": {"id": "chatcmpl-DHxpM95dc6kebbAbEOjaMmB5PFgfr", "choices": [{"finish_reason": "tool_calls", "index": 0, "logprobs": null, "message": {"content": "To build a REST API for a todo app, we need to execute the project in a series of stages, including defining the architecture, engineering the solution, reviewing the code, and testing it. Here is how we will break down the project into tasks:\n\n1. **Architectural Design**:\n   - Determine the API endpoints and structure.\n   - Identify the data model and storage mechanism.\n   - Define authentication and authorization if required.\n\n2. **Engineering**:\n   - Implement the API endpoints.\n   - Connect to the database or storage.\n   - Implement authentication and any other business logic.\n\n3. **Code Review**:\n   - Review the code for best practices and adherence to the design.\n   - Ensure proper error handling and response status codes.\n\n4. **Quality Assurance (QA)**:\n   - Test the API endpoints for expected behavior.\n   - Validate against edge cases and security vulnerabilities.\n\nLet's begin by defining the architectural components. I'll assign this task to the Architect.", "refusal": null, "role": "assistant", "annotations": [], "audio": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_UusEEed1WickyNLUjbiqqFWq", "function": {"arguments": "{\"path\":\"/\"}", "name": "docs_list_directory"}, "type": "function"}]}}], "created": 1773173924, "model": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "object": "chat.completion", "service_tier": "default", "system_fingerprint": "fp_c4e01d72e0", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 212, "prompt_tokens": 408, "total_tokens": 620, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 0}}}, "prompt_tokens": 408, "completion_tokens": 212, "agent_id": "ProjectManager_144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee/144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee"}
2026-03-11 03:18:49,980 [INFO] autogen_core: Publishing message of type GroupChatMessage to all subscribers: {'message': ThoughtEvent(id='c9596ccd-9c6d-4d00-932a-c8308c397534', source='ProjectManager', models_usage=None, metadata={}, created_at=datetime.datetime(2026, 3, 10, 20, 18, 49, 980523, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), content="To build a REST API for a todo app, we need to execute the project in a series of stages, including defining the architecture, engineering the solution, reviewing the code, and testing it. Here is how we will break down the project into tasks:\n\n1. **Architectural Design**:\n   - Determine the API endpoints and structure.\n   - Identify the data model and storage mechanism.\n   - Define authentication and authorization if required.\n\n2. **Engineering**:\n   - Implement the API endpoints.\n   - Connect to the database or storage.\n   - Implement authentication and any other business logic.\n\n3. **Code Review**:\n   - Review the code for best practices and adherence to the design.\n   - Ensure proper error handling and response status codes.\n\n4. **Quality Assurance (QA)**:\n   - Test the API endpoints for expected behavior.\n   - Validate against edge cases and security vulnerabilities.\n\nLet's begin by defining the architectural components. I'll assign this task to the Architect.", type='ThoughtEvent')}
2026-03-11 03:18:49,981 [INFO] autogen_core.events: {"payload": "{\"message\":{\"id\":\"c9596ccd-9c6d-4d00-932a-c8308c397534\",\"source\":\"ProjectManager\",\"models_usage\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"created_at\":\"2026-03-10T20:18:49.980523Z\",\"content\":\"To build a REST API for a todo app, we need to execute the project in a series of stages, including defining the architecture, engineering the solution, reviewing the code, and testing it. Here is how we will break down the project into tasks:\\n\\n1. **Architectural Design**:\\n   - Determine the API endpoints and structure.\\n   - Identify the data model and storage mechanism.\\n   - Define authentication and authorization if required.\\n\\n2. **Engineering**:\\n   - Implement the API endpoints.\\n   - Connect to the database or storage.\\n   - Implement authentication and any other business logic.\\n\\n3. **Code Review**:\\n   - Review the code for best practices and adherence to the design.\\n   - Ensure proper error handling and response status codes.\\n\\n4. **Quality Assurance (QA)**:\\n   - Test the API endpoints for expected behavior.\\n   - Validate against edge cases and security vulnerabilities.\\n\\nLet's begin by defining the architectural components. I'll assign this task to the Architect.\",\"type\":\"ThoughtEvent\"}}", "sender": "ProjectManager_144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee/144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee", "receiver": "output_topic_144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee/144600d9-f5fe-44f5-bc1a-d2de79b388ee", "kind": "MessageKind.PUBLISH", "delivery_stage": "DeliveryStage.SEND", "type": "Message"}
